The paper discusses the acceleration of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The paper also mentions the challenges associated with hardware acceleration, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for GAN acceleration, which involves reordering computations and creating distinct microprograms, which could fall under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
